  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>When President Obama and President Xi Jinping meet next week in Beijing, climate change and energy will be important topics of discussion. As the world&#8217;s two biggest emitters, leadership by the U.S. and China is critical as each country&#8217;s actions are closely watched by the other and the international community. In addition, interest was heightened when a senior Chinese official talked about the possibility of peak emissions in China at the UN Climate Summit in September.</p></div>
